257
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:31,896
Everything.

258
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,398
We replaced the entire
exhaust system.

259
00:15:33,632 --> 00:15:37,101
- Barely made the difference.
- Are you using magnesium parts?

260
00:15:49,982 --> 00:15:51,149
Now the engine block.

261
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:54,085
Any mounting or fixing plates,
strip it out also.

262
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,520
When you've done that,

263
00:15:55,754 --> 00:15:57,455
we have to look
at the aerodynamics,

264
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:59,257
front and rear wing.

265
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:18,810
Okay, thank you.
Good night.

266
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:41,099
What was Regazzoni's time?

267
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:43,601
1:53.

268
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,904
Okay, now put him in my car
and he'll go 2 seconds faster.

269
00:16:47,139 --> 00:16:49,974
- Well, that's impossible.
- No chance.

270
00:16:52,277 --> 00:16:55,013
We've been working on it
all night.

271
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:57,482
Put Regazzoni in the car.
See what happens.

272
00:16:57,716 --> 00:16:58,950
I don't understand.
Why am I supposed to do this?

273
00:16:59,184 --> 00:16:59,951
I don't know, Clay.

274
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:02,553
He wants you
to take it for a spin.

275
00:17:03,756 --> 00:17:04,956
Gloves, please.

276
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:53,438
- I'd say we push it...
- All right.

277
00:17:53,672 --> 00:17:55,706
What did you do to the car?

278
00:17:55,941 --> 00:17:57,542
That's information
I'll share with you

279
00:17:57,776 --> 00:17:59,510
under certain conditions only.

280
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:00,645
Go on.

281
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,781
A guaranteed place in the team.

282
00:18:04,016 --> 00:18:05,483
And a paid contract
on equal terms

283
00:18:05,717 --> 00:18:07,785
with Regazzoni for two years.

284
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,320
Are you crazy?

285
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:11,689
Clay's a senior figure in F1.

286
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,357
You're just a rookie!

287
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:16,027
The only reason we took you on
is because you're paying us.

288
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:18,396
Well, as of now,
if you want me to stay,

289
00:18:18,630 --> 00:18:20,898
we rip up the contract,
I don't pay you a cent.

290
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:22,733
That's outrageous!

291
00:18:22,968 --> 00:18:25,103
Was he quicker in my car?

292
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:27,538
He was, wasn't he?

293
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:30,641
Did he go two seconds faster?

294
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,413
Two point three.

295
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,585
So, have a think,

296
00:18:40,819 --> 00:18:43,821
work out your priorities
and get back to me.

297
00:18:58,237 --> 00:18:59,170
Hey, Niki.

298
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:05,009
I know what you're going to say,
that it's none of my business.

299
00:19:05,244 --> 00:19:06,077
What?

300
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:10,848
If it's the track manager you're
taking on your date tonight.

301
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,451
It's none of your business.

302
00:19:13,685 --> 00:19:15,686
Okay, but if you want my advice,

303
00:19:15,921 --> 00:19:17,588
I'd let this one go.

304
00:19:18,524 --> 00:19:21,726
I'm not questioning your taste.
She is a great girl, but...

305
00:19:23,795 --> 00:19:25,830
Agnes's last boyfriend

306
00:19:26,064 --> 00:19:27,999
was a British Formula 2 driver

307
00:19:28,233 --> 00:19:30,401
who has a reputation
for two things,

308
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:32,970
for being a little crazy
on the track...

309
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:35,706
and for going all night
and all day

310
00:19:35,941 --> 00:19:38,409
and all night again in bed.
He's a good driver,

311
00:19:38,644 --> 00:19:40,778
but an immortal fuck apparently.

312
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,713
I don't know about you,
but that's not an act

313
00:19:42,948 --> 00:19:44,849
I'd like to follow.

314
00:19:46,985 --> 00:19:49,620
But if that
doesn't bother you...

315
00:19:51,056 --> 00:19:53,724
What's his name, the driver?

316
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:56,427
Hunt. James Hunt.

317
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:02,400
You see, you share information

318
00:20:02,634 --> 00:20:04,502
and I share information.

319
00:20:04,836 --> 00:20:07,138
That's what teammates are for.

320
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:20,818
- Where the hell are we going?
- I promise it'll be worth it.

321
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,853
Just keep them closed.

322
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:26,624
Wait for it.

323
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:31,462
There.

324
00:20:31,697 --> 00:20:32,830
What do you say?

325
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:34,732
She's Formula 1.

326
00:20:35,033 --> 00:20:37,134
Yes, she is, Superstar.

327
00:20:37,369 --> 00:20:40,071
Your brother and I got together
with the bean counters.

328
00:20:40,305 --> 00:20:42,139
And since the economics
of F1 are not

329
00:20:42,374 --> 00:20:44,842
so significantly different
to the economics of F2,

330
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,745
well, we thought if we were
going to be losing money,

331
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:50,881
we might as well be doing it
on the big roulette table in F1.

332
00:20:51,116 --> 00:20:54,252
You fat, little, inbred beauty.
Come here.

333
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:02,093
Actually, credit where it's due,
we got the idea from Niki.

334
00:21:02,327 --> 00:21:03,694
- Who?
- Lauda.

335
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:06,097
Bought his way in
rather than mess about

336
00:21:06,331 --> 00:21:07,498
in the lower divisions.
I thought:

337
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:08,799
"Bloody hell, he's right."

338
00:21:09,034 --> 00:21:10,701
No sponsorship, Superstar.

339
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,069
I hope you approve.

340
00:21:12,304 --> 00:21:15,906
No vulgar logos
for cigarettes or condoms.

341
00:21:16,675 --> 00:21:18,609
Just plain white with the flags.

342
00:21:18,844 --> 00:21:20,778
And racing overalls

343
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:22,913
which read:

344
00:21:23,515 --> 00:21:26,183
"Sex. Breakfast of champions."

345
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:30,154
So when do we start?

346
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:33,824
- Soon as you're ready.
- Ready?

347
00:21:34,059 --> 00:21:36,594
I've been waiting for this
my whole life.

348
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:39,830
VILLAGE OF
WATKINS GLEN

349
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:49,674
When the season started,
people wondered

350
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:51,542
whether Lord Hesketh
and his team

351
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:53,944
of upper-class enthusiasts
were bringing glamour

352
00:21:54,179 --> 00:21:56,847
to the racing community
or just comedy.

353
00:21:57,215 --> 00:21:59,483
Certainly it was the first time
anyone had seen

354
00:21:59,718 --> 00:22:02,720
a butler serving oysters
and caviar in the pits.

355
00:22:03,021 --> 00:22:05,790
But they have made
quite an impact.

356
00:22:06,024 --> 00:22:09,393
6th in France, 4th in Britain
and 3rd in Holland.

357
00:22:09,628 --> 00:22:12,530
All drivers on the track,
caution flags are out.

358
00:22:12,764 --> 00:22:15,066
A severe crash at the Esses.

359
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,501
Red flag.
There's a car off the track.

360
00:22:17,736 --> 00:22:19,503
And reports are reaching me
that there's been

361
00:22:19,738 --> 00:22:21,739
a serious accident
in qualifying.

362
00:22:21,973 --> 00:22:23,941
The identity of the driver
we don't currently have,

363
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:26,811
but as you can tell from
all the activity going on

364
00:22:27,045 --> 00:22:30,548
towards the track, it was
clearly a grave incident indeed.

365
00:22:30,782 --> 00:22:33,117
We will, of course, have
more information as we get it,

366
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:36,687
but it is the sight and sound
of F1 nobody likes to see.

367
00:22:41,226 --> 00:22:43,694
- Get your hands off me!
- Hey, come on!

368
00:22:53,071 --> 00:22:56,474
Drivers of top stature we've
lost just in the past 4 seasons

369
00:22:56,708 --> 00:22:58,776
have included Piers Courage,

370
00:22:59,077 --> 00:23:00,144
Jochen Rindt,

371
00:23:01,046 --> 00:23:02,213
Jo Siffert,

372
00:23:03,181 --> 00:23:04,515
Roger Williamson

373
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,650
and today, at Watkins Glen,

374
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:09,653
Formula 1 has claimed
another driver.

375
00:23:09,988 --> 00:23:12,590
The Tyrrell team
have withdrawn from the race.

376
00:23:12,824 --> 00:23:14,892
Their places on the grid
will be left empty.

377
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:17,561
- Terrible.
- They should cancel the race.

378
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:18,662
Why?

379
00:23:19,197 --> 00:23:22,066
He made a mistake,
went into the corner too fast.

380
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:23,434
It's his fault.

381
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:25,669
- Is that right?
- It's obvious.

382
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,738
Look at the tyre marks.

383
00:23:27,973 --> 00:23:31,075
So says the nobody, who had
to pay for his own drive.

384
00:23:31,309 --> 00:23:33,010
How's that working out for you,
by the way?

385
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:34,211
Fine.

386
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:36,547
How is it at the back?

387
00:23:36,782 --> 00:23:39,116
Not planning
on being there for long.

388
00:23:40,018 --> 00:23:42,753
Ten minutes to the warm-up lap.
Ten minutes.

389
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:43,854
Asshole.

390
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,258
Arsehole.

391
00:23:48,994 --> 00:23:52,196
Heading into the Grand Hotel
hairpin, second gear.

392
00:23:52,431 --> 00:23:55,199
Turn in hard,
looking for late apex,

393
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:56,967
gentle with the bar.

394
00:23:57,803 --> 00:24:00,004
Heading into Portier,
second gear,

395
00:24:00,238 --> 00:24:01,338
clip the apex,

396
00:24:01,573 --> 00:24:03,073
light brake, stay in second,

397
00:24:03,308 --> 00:24:04,975
looking for a good exit.

398
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:06,911
Heading through the tunnel,
gradual right,

399
00:24:07,145 --> 00:24:09,880
up through third,
fourth, fifth...

400
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,816
Is Alexander around?

401
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:14,585
Yes, he was.

402
00:24:15,153 --> 00:24:17,021
He went back to the house
to take a call.

403
00:24:17,255 --> 00:24:18,722
He'll be back shortly.

404
00:24:18,957 --> 00:24:21,725
He only wanted to show me
his pride and joy.

405
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:24,428
Rhymes with 'boy'
if you ask me.

406
00:24:24,663 --> 00:24:25,796
And 'toy.'

407
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:28,132
God, it's so flimsy.

408
00:24:28,366 --> 00:24:30,734
For something
that costs so much.

409
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:34,538
There's no comfort,
no protection, nothing.

410
00:24:34,906 --> 00:24:37,475
No, it's just
a little coffin, really.

411
00:24:37,709 --> 00:24:40,478
Surrounded by
high-octane fuel in here.

412
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:43,481
Being driven round 170 mph.

413
00:24:43,815 --> 00:24:47,117
To all intents and purposes,
this thing's a bomb on wheels.

414
00:24:47,986 --> 00:24:49,954
You're James, aren't you?

415
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:52,256
Yes.

416
00:24:53,725 --> 00:24:55,626
You fit the description.

417
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,228
Is that right?

418
00:24:58,296 --> 00:25:00,431
Suzy. Friend ofAlex's.

419
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:01,732
Yeah, yeah.

420
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,801
I know exactly.

421
00:25:05,237 --> 00:25:06,971
What was the description?

422
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:08,639
Mostly positive in terms
of appearance.

423
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:10,841
Negative only in terms
of character.

424
00:25:11,076 --> 00:25:13,410
I've been told to avoid you.

425
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:14,812
By whom?

426
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:16,614
Alexander.

427
00:25:16,848 --> 00:25:18,649
He says you're a bad boy.

428
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:20,751
Alexander doesn't know
what he's talking about.

429
00:25:20,986 --> 00:25:22,820
I was. I'm not anymore.

430
00:25:23,054 --> 00:25:24,889
The new me is very professional.

431
00:25:25,123 --> 00:25:26,624
Early to bed, early to rise.

432
00:25:26,858 --> 00:25:28,058
All very dull,

433
00:25:28,493 --> 00:25:29,793
but according to the team,

434
00:25:30,028 --> 00:25:32,930
'the best way to keep
beating the goose stepper.'

435
00:25:33,164 --> 00:25:34,865
Is that what you were doing
when I came in?

436
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,801
Yes, visualization techniques,
memorising the circuit,

437
00:25:38,036 --> 00:25:40,638
in this case Monaco,
which is up next.

438
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:47,845
Personally I've always been
a great believer

439
00:25:48,079 --> 00:25:49,780
in getting there on the day,
putting my foot down

440
00:25:50,015 --> 00:25:52,116
and playing chicken
with everyone else.

441
00:25:53,652 --> 00:25:55,085
But they don't want me
doing that anymore.

442
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:58,822
They want my body like a temple
and my mind like a monk.

443
00:25:59,691 --> 00:26:02,059
And what about your soul,
your heart?

444
00:26:02,294 --> 00:26:04,562
They've got ideas
about that, too.

445
00:26:05,030 --> 00:26:07,031
They want me to stop
messing around,

446
00:26:07,265 --> 00:26:10,367
settle down, get married
with the next nice girl I meet.

447
00:26:10,602 --> 00:26:12,570
They think
that'd be good for me.

448
00:26:12,804 --> 00:26:14,071
What do you think?

449
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:16,206
It sounds fucking awful.

450
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:21,111
But sine they're right
about most things,

451
00:26:21,346 --> 00:26:23,681
they're probably right
about that too.

452
00:26:24,015 --> 00:26:26,917
You don't fancy
getting married, do you?

453
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:52,943
Suzy.

454
00:26:53,812 --> 00:26:55,512
JUST MARRIED

455
00:26:56,014 --> 00:26:57,982
Hey, hey, hey!

456
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:03,621
- What's going on with him?
- Nothing. Nothing.

457
00:27:03,855 --> 00:27:05,623
Didn't want to ruin your day.

458
00:27:05,857 --> 00:27:06,857
It's...

459
00:27:07,192 --> 00:27:09,627
- it's the Kraut.
- What about him?

460
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:12,730
He's just been signed
by Ferrari.

461
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:14,698
You're kidding me?

462
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:16,767
Jesus. How did that happen?

463
00:27:17,002 --> 00:27:18,569
Did he buy his way in there too?

464
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:21,438
Well, the old man took
Regazzoni back

465
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:23,641
and he insisted on it
apparently.

466
00:27:23,875 --> 00:27:26,944
He says that Niki's a genius
setting up the cars.

467
00:27:45,263 --> 00:27:47,598
It's terrible.
Drives like a pig.

468
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:50,501
- You can't say that.
- Why not?

469
00:27:50,735 --> 00:27:53,003
- It's a Ferrari!
- It's a shitbox!

470
00:27:53,238 --> 00:27:55,039
It understeers like crazy
and the weight distribution

471
00:27:55,273 --> 00:27:56,507
is a disaster.

472
00:27:56,741 --> 00:27:57,908
It's amazing,
all these facilities

473
00:27:58,143 --> 00:28:00,444
and you make a piece of crap
like this.

474
00:28:30,975 --> 00:28:32,543
"Ferrari family,"

475
00:28:32,777 --> 00:28:34,344
"our good friend
Clay Regazzoni."

476
00:28:34,579 --> 00:28:36,680
You are family and friend
to the commendatore

477
00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:38,015
as long as you win.

478
00:28:38,249 --> 00:28:39,616
The minute you don't,
ciao, ciao.

479
00:28:39,851 --> 00:28:41,118
I totally understand.

480
00:28:41,352 --> 00:28:42,519
It's business.

481
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:43,921
I would do the same.

482
00:28:44,155 --> 00:28:46,123
But it isn't
just business, is it?

483
00:28:46,357 --> 00:28:48,759
What we do.
It's passion, love.

484
00:28:48,993 --> 00:28:51,729
Which is why we are prepared
to risk our lives for it.

485
00:28:51,963 --> 00:28:52,763
Not me.

486
00:28:52,997 --> 00:28:54,932
If I had more talent
and could earn better money

487
00:28:55,166 --> 00:28:57,401
with something else,
I would.

488
00:28:57,635 --> 00:28:59,403
How do you know you will
make money here?

489
00:28:59,637 --> 00:29:01,071
You haven't yet.

490
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:03,373
Not yet, but I will.

491
00:29:03,975 --> 00:29:06,543
If you can, I can.

492
00:29:09,814 --> 00:29:12,716
You know, are you ever
not an asshole?

493
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:14,952
- Why am I an asshole?
- Well...

494
00:29:15,186 --> 00:29:18,522
By now I'm both quicker than you
and better at setting up a car.

495
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:20,791
You can't deal with it,
so you're the asshole.

496
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:22,159
Screw you.

497
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:30,834
I brought you along today

498
00:29:31,069 --> 00:29:32,870
because you seem
like a lonely kind of guy.

499
00:29:33,104 --> 00:29:35,038
I thought if I introduced you
to some nice people,

500
00:29:35,273 --> 00:29:36,740
that could rub off on you.

501
00:29:36,975 --> 00:29:37,908
Forget it.

502
00:29:38,143 --> 00:29:39,543
Make your own friends.

503
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:40,978
Come on, Clay.

504
00:29:41,212 --> 00:29:42,479
I'm sorry.

505
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:19,650
Are you leaving?

506
00:30:20,552 --> 00:30:21,485
Yes.

507
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:23,887
Can you give me a lift
to the nearest town,

508
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:26,523
anywhere with a train station?

509
00:30:26,958 --> 00:30:27,891
Sure.

510
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,727
Trento's half an hour's drive.

511
00:30:30,962 --> 00:30:31,862
Get in.

512
00:30:58,923 --> 00:31:00,457
What are you doing?

513
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:02,526
You hear that noise
when you accelerate?

514
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:04,795
- No.
- Your fan belt is loose.

515
00:31:05,029 --> 00:31:06,129
