01:08:02,878 --> 01:08:04,846
Mass passing Lauda now!

1010
01:08:05,081 --> 01:08:08,883
Jochen Mass, in the number 12
McLaren, takes the lead!

1011
01:08:09,118 --> 01:08:11,619
Jochen Mass, the clear leader,
with everybody else

1012
01:08:11,854 --> 01:08:13,788
making the decision
to change tyres

1013
01:08:14,023 --> 01:08:15,523
after just one lap of this race.

1014
01:08:15,758 --> 01:08:17,492
Come on, let's go!

1015
01:08:25,668 --> 01:08:29,504
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should've taken my advice.

1016
01:08:29,738 --> 01:08:31,739
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

1017
01:08:31,974 --> 01:08:34,976
Behind you.
He made the same mistake.

1018
01:08:46,856 --> 01:08:47,822
Come on!

1019
01:08:51,293 --> 01:08:53,895
Come on! What's going on?

1020
01:08:54,230 --> 01:08:57,899
The tyre-changing frenzy caused
a huge reshuffling of the pack,

1021
01:08:58,134 --> 01:09:00,835
- with Mass in the lead now.
- You're clear. Go!

1022
01:09:03,706 --> 01:09:05,874
Lauda urging
his mechanics to hurry.

1023
01:09:08,744 --> 01:09:11,479
It's a disaster! Come on!

1024
01:09:22,458 --> 01:09:24,092
What's going on, you assholes?

1025
01:09:47,583 --> 01:09:50,118
This race has gone wrong
for him so far.

1026
01:09:50,352 --> 01:09:52,053
His championship rival,
James Hunt,

1027
01:09:52,288 --> 01:09:54,189
is a long way up the road.

1028
01:10:04,567 --> 01:10:06,768
Lauda passing car after car.
He's just going past

1029
01:10:07,002 --> 01:10:09,137
Mario Andretti's Lotus there.

1030
01:10:56,118 --> 01:10:57,051
Niki!

1031
01:11:02,891 --> 01:11:04,192
Get me out!

1032
01:11:04,493 --> 01:11:05,426
Help me!

1033
01:11:08,163 --> 01:11:09,931
Several cars are involved.

1034
01:11:10,165 --> 01:11:12,433
Looks like it might be
one of the Ferraris.

1035
01:11:19,608 --> 01:11:21,909
- Come this way!
- Come on, come on!

1036
01:11:34,223 --> 01:11:35,590
Keep trying.

1037
01:11:42,798 --> 01:11:44,899
- Come this way.
- Okay.

1038
01:13:22,898 --> 01:13:25,633
The flood, which swept down
Big Thompson Canyon in Colorado,

1039
01:13:25,868 --> 01:13:28,069
was the worst
since records began.

1040
01:13:28,303 --> 01:13:30,838
In Formula 1 today,
victory celebrations were muted

1041
01:13:31,073 --> 01:13:33,040
after a horrific accident
involving world champion

1042
01:13:33,275 --> 01:13:34,742
Niki Lauda.

1043
01:13:34,977 --> 01:13:36,778
Due to safety concerns
before the race,

1044
01:13:37,012 --> 01:13:39,080
the Austrian had said
he would not take part,

1045
01:13:39,314 --> 01:13:41,149
but in the end he did.

1046
01:13:41,984 --> 01:13:44,452
He was making up for lost
time when he went off the track,

1047
01:13:44,686 --> 01:13:46,788
puncturing the Ferrari's
fuel tank.

1048
01:13:47,022 --> 01:13:49,757
Brett Lunger was unable
to avoid the flaming wreck

1049
01:13:49,992 --> 01:13:52,693
but was unhurt and joined
other drivers to rescue Lauda,

1050
01:13:52,928 --> 01:13:55,730
who was taken to Manheim
Hospital with severe burns,

1051
01:13:55,964 --> 01:13:59,367
the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.

1052
01:13:59,601 --> 01:14:01,469
Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute

1053
01:14:01,703 --> 01:14:04,639
in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.

1054
01:15:07,002 --> 01:15:09,170
14 DAYS LATER

1055
01:15:56,919 --> 01:15:59,787
28th DAY IN HOSPITAL
29th AUGUST 1976

1056
01:18:44,152 --> 01:18:47,655
ITALIAN GRAND PRIX
FREE PRACTICE SEPTEMBER 1976

1057
01:18:50,926 --> 01:18:53,160
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

1058
01:18:53,395 --> 01:18:54,595
Looking good.

1059
01:18:58,200 --> 01:19:00,634
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

1060
01:19:00,869 --> 01:19:02,837
- What about him?
- He's here.

1061
01:19:03,071 --> 01:19:04,839
- What?
- He's racing.

1062
01:19:20,088 --> 01:19:21,021
Niki.

1063
01:19:28,130 --> 01:19:29,730
It's that bad, huh?

1064
01:19:30,832 --> 01:19:31,766
No.

1065
01:19:33,135 --> 01:19:36,537
In hospital, I asked them
straight, no bullshit,

1066
01:19:36,772 --> 01:19:39,373
how bad my appearance would be.

1067
01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:42,343
They said with time
it would be fine.

1068
01:19:42,577 --> 01:19:43,811
But it won't.

1069
01:19:44,946 --> 01:19:47,948
I can tell,
seeing your reaction.

1070
01:19:48,884 --> 01:19:50,618
I'll spend the rest of my life

1071
01:19:50,852 --> 01:19:53,554
with a face
that frightens people.

1072
01:19:55,924 --> 01:19:59,160
You know, Niki, I tried to write
you a letter at the time,

1073
01:19:59,394 --> 01:20:00,761
to apologise.

1074
01:20:01,530 --> 01:20:04,064
The drivers' meeting in Germany,
before the race.

1075
01:20:04,299 --> 01:20:06,934
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

1076
01:20:07,169 --> 01:20:09,703
That race should never
have gone ahead.

1077
01:20:09,938 --> 01:20:11,572
No, it shouldn't.

1078
01:20:11,807 --> 01:20:15,509
So in many ways I feel
responsible for what happened...

1079
01:20:15,744 --> 01:20:16,877
You were.

1080
01:20:18,713 --> 01:20:19,914
But, trust me,

1081
01:20:21,550 --> 01:20:23,651
watching you win those races,

1082
01:20:23,885 --> 01:20:26,253
while I was fighting
for my life...

1083
01:20:27,856 --> 01:20:31,492
you were equally responsible
for getting me back in the car.

1084
01:20:58,887 --> 01:21:01,488
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

1085
01:21:02,023 --> 01:21:02,890
Niki,

1086
01:21:03,124 --> 01:21:06,460
can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you had

1087
01:21:06,695 --> 01:21:08,462
and the expectations
for you recovery?

1088
01:21:08,697 --> 01:21:09,563
Sure.

1089
01:21:09,898 --> 01:21:11,765
I had a skin graft operation

1090
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:14,768
where they put half
my right thigh in my face.

1091
01:21:16,037 --> 01:21:18,572
Now, it doesn't look too good,

1092
01:21:18,807 --> 01:21:20,841
but one unexpected advantage is

1093
01:21:21,076 --> 01:21:23,010
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

1094
01:21:23,245 --> 01:21:25,412
so sweat will never run
into my eyes again,

1095
01:21:25,647 --> 01:21:27,882
which is good for a driver.

1096
01:21:28,984 --> 01:21:30,885
When they heard about
your condition,

1097
01:21:31,119 --> 01:21:33,520
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver,

1098
01:21:33,755 --> 01:21:34,788
Carlos Reutemann.

1099
01:21:35,023 --> 01:21:38,492
Yeah, before ever reaching
the hospital.

1100
01:21:38,994 --> 01:21:42,229
- Is Reutemann driving today too?
- Yes.

1101
01:21:42,731 --> 01:21:44,665
And keen to make an impression.

1102
01:21:44,900 --> 01:21:46,667
So let's see where
Mr. Reutemann finishes

1103
01:21:46,902 --> 01:21:49,103
and where I finish today.

1104
01:21:49,771 --> 01:21:51,639
James Hunt and McLaren
have caught up a lot

1105
01:21:51,873 --> 01:21:53,607
while you were away.

1106
01:21:53,842 --> 01:21:54,675
Yes.

1107
01:21:55,277 --> 01:21:56,944
So is there a question now

1108
01:21:57,178 --> 01:21:59,980
or are you just trying
to piss me off?

1109
01:22:01,650 --> 01:22:03,918
You still think you can win?

1110
01:22:04,152 --> 01:22:05,619
Yes, of course.

1111
01:22:05,854 --> 01:22:07,221
I have the better car.

1112
01:22:07,789 --> 01:22:10,457
And possibly
I'm the better driver.

1113
01:22:10,692 --> 01:22:13,027
But he's a clever guy
and he's used his time well

1114
01:22:13,261 --> 01:22:15,696
while I was lying
half-dead in hospital

1115
01:22:15,931 --> 01:22:17,631
to win some points.

1116
01:22:18,900 --> 01:22:22,436
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1117
01:22:27,776 --> 01:22:29,543
She said, "Sweetie,

1118
01:22:29,911 --> 01:22:32,947
you don't need a face to drive.
You just need the right foot."

1119
01:22:34,549 --> 01:22:35,916
I'm being serious.

1120
01:22:36,551 --> 01:22:39,153
Do you really think
your marriage can survive

1121
01:22:39,387 --> 01:22:41,755
with the way you look now?

1122
01:22:43,625 --> 01:22:45,659
And I'm being serious too.

1123
01:22:46,328 --> 01:22:47,528
Fuck you.

1124
01:22:48,196 --> 01:22:50,097
Press conference over.

1125
01:22:54,903 --> 01:22:58,038
- That was hairy.
- You know how to get noticed.

1126
01:22:58,273 --> 01:22:59,840
I thought it went well,
to be honest.

1127
01:23:00,075 --> 01:23:01,809
They don't like it
when it's not going their way.

1128
01:23:02,043 --> 01:23:03,444
That's the game.

1129
01:23:03,678 --> 01:23:05,579
- See you.
- See you later.

1130
01:23:05,814 --> 01:23:07,781
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1131
01:23:08,016 --> 01:23:10,484
I think I've got something
for you on that last question,

1132
01:23:10,719 --> 01:23:12,786
- about Niki.
- You heard about that?

1133
01:23:14,823 --> 01:23:15,756
James?

1134
01:23:24,232 --> 01:23:25,933
Please, James...

1135
01:23:26,234 --> 01:23:29,870
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1136
01:23:32,307 --> 01:23:33,240
Prick.

1137
01:23:50,091 --> 01:23:52,493
So Niki Lauda, just 42 days

1138
01:23:52,727 --> 01:23:55,095
after his near-fatal accident
at Nrburgring,

1139
01:23:55,330 --> 01:23:56,764
will race here today, at Monza

1140
01:23:56,998 --> 01:24:00,701
against all medical advice
and no doubt in incredible pain.

1141
01:24:05,473 --> 01:24:08,809
Photographers, please,
clear the grid.

1142
01:24:46,181 --> 01:24:47,948
Niki, it's time.

1143
01:24:49,918 --> 01:24:50,851
Okay?

1144
01:24:57,926 --> 01:24:59,827
Please, clear the grid.

1145
01:25:02,030 --> 01:25:03,964
One minute to go.

1146
01:25:50,211 --> 01:25:53,013
The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.

1147
01:25:53,248 --> 01:25:55,983
He's been overtaken
by car after car.

1148
01:26:05,160 --> 01:26:08,428
Lauda's off line.
He runs wide onto the grass.

1149
01:26:13,468 --> 01:26:15,402
He wrestles it back
onto the track,

1150
01:26:15,637 --> 01:26:17,804
but that was a bad moment
for Niki.

1151
01:26:22,010 --> 01:26:24,111
Niki Lauda's the reigning
world champion,

1152
01:26:24,345 --> 01:26:27,347
but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,

1153
01:26:27,582 --> 01:26:30,517
to himself and to the rest
of the field.

1154
01:26:32,020 --> 01:26:35,989
And Stuck has collided
with Mario Andretti's Lotus!

1155
01:26:36,224 --> 01:26:39,059
Niki's boxed in!
He's got nowhere to go!

1156
01:26:53,841 --> 01:26:55,909
Niki Lauda's actually
making a move.

1157
01:26:56,144 --> 01:26:58,145
He's on Brambilla's tail.

1158
01:27:00,682 --> 01:27:03,684
He pulls out of the slipstream
to overtake.

1159
01:27:03,918 --> 01:27:05,886
Lauda's starting
to find the form

1160
01:27:06,120 --> 01:27:08,822
that early in this race
we believed he'd lost.

1161
01:27:14,896 --> 01:27:17,464
Lauda's now lapping faster
than Reutemann

1162
01:27:17,699 --> 01:27:19,733
and closing the gap ahead.

1163
01:27:22,870 --> 01:27:25,105
Lauda closing
on Carlos Reutemann,

1164
01:27:25,340 --> 01:27:27,474
the man called in to be
his replacement

1165
01:27:27,709 --> 01:27:29,142
in the Ferrari team.

1166
01:27:37,752 --> 01:27:39,753
And there's James Hunt's
McLaren,

1167
01:27:39,988 --> 01:27:43,156
smoking stationary
by the side of the road.

1168
01:27:45,593 --> 01:27:48,862
This is bad news for Hunt's
championship hopes.

1169
01:27:53,568 --> 01:27:54,901
It's Ronnie Peterson

1170
01:27:55,136 --> 01:27:57,371
who comes home the winner
here at Monza.

1171
01:27:57,605 --> 01:28:00,574
But all eyes are on the man
who finishes a brilliant fourth!

1172
01:28:01,109 --> 01:28:02,542
Niki Lauda!

1173
01:28:44,052 --> 01:28:46,453
What a race, what a man,
what a season.

1174
01:28:46,688 --> 01:28:48,622
With a 4th-place finish
and three priceless points,

1175
01:28:48,856 --> 01:28:50,724
Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1176
01:28:50,958 --> 01:28:53,627
to retaining
the World Championship.

1177
01:29:51,486 --> 01:29:54,921
So the long, grueling
and incredibly dramatic season

1178
01:29:55,156 --> 01:29:57,858
comes down to this final race
in Japan,

1179
01:29:58,092 --> 01:30:00,494
in the shadow of Mount Fuji.

1180
01:30:00,828 --> 01:30:03,830
Niki Lauda goes into
this deciding race at Fuji

1181
01:30:04,065 --> 01:30:06,133
just three points ahead
of James Hunt,

1182
01:30:06,367 --> 01:30:09,136
Hunt knowing he must beat
the Austrian fair and square

1183
01:30:09,370 --> 01:30:10,937
to take the title.

1184
01:30:12,006 --> 01:30:15,475
James, do you think
you can cope with the pressure?

1185
01:30:15,710 --> 01:30:17,844
Well, I've never really
understood what that means.

1186
01:30:18,079 --> 01:30:21,081
I love my job.
I love competing. I love racing.

1187
01:30:22,083 --> 01:30:24,184
Maybe you should ask Niki.
He's the World Champion.

1188
01:30:24,419 --> 01:30:25,819
He's got everything to lose.

1189
01:30:26,053 --> 01:30:28,121
Mr. Lauda,
are you feeling pressure?

1190
01:30:28,356 --> 01:30:30,824
Do I look like
I'm feeling pressure?

1191
01:30:32,627 --> 01:30:33,894
I'm World Champion

1192
01:30:34,128 --> 01:30:36,963
and on the verge to become
World Champion again.

1193
01:30:37,198 --> 01:30:39,399
Hunt now has
the opportunity to win,

1194
01:30:39,634 --> 01:30:41,168
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1195
01:30:41,402 --> 01:30:44,004
You have to really believe it
to make it possible.

1196
01:30:44,338 --> 01:30:46,640
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1197
01:30:46,874 --> 01:30:49,075
If Niki is being tricky
and getting a kicky

1198
01:30:49,310 --> 01:30:51,478
out of playing mind games,

1199
01:30:51,712 --> 01:30:53,146
then fine, I'm flattered.

1200
01:30:53,381 --> 01:30:56,650
The fact is momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1201
01:30:57,051 --> 01:30:59,386
I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1202
01:30:59,620 --> 01:31:01,121
will be with me
as World Champion.

1203
01:31:05,760 --> 01:31:08,128
Intermittent heavy rain
has been forecast

1204
01:31:08,362 --> 01:31:11,031
here at Fuji today,
along with strong winds

1205
01:31:11,265 --> 01:31:12,599
and occasional fog

1206
01:31:12,834 --> 01:31:14,968
rolling in from the mountain.

1207
01:31:16,771 --> 01:31:19,139
And so with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come,

1208
01:31:19,373 --> 01:31:21,608
Lauda's lead
a mere three points.

1209
01:31:21,843 --> 01:31:23,477
What a way to finish the season.

1210
01:31:23,711 --> 01:31:24,878
Hunt or Lauda?

1211
01:31:25,112 --> 01:31:27,547
The final chapter will unfold
when we bring you

1212
01:31:27,782 --> 01:31:29,850
- extended coverage...
- They've got to cancel the race.

1213
01:31:30,084 --> 01:31:31,184
It's lethal out there.

1214
01:31:31,419 --> 01:31:33,086
The race is going ahead.

1215
01:31:33,321 --> 01:31:35,589
Television rights have been
sold all around the world.

1216
01:31:35,823 --> 01:31:36,957
The showdown
between you and Niki

1217
01:31:37,191 --> 01:31:38,558
is all anyone wants to see.

1218
01:31:38,793 --> 01:31:41,661
With heavy rain continuing
to fall here at Fuji,

1219
01:31:41,896 --> 01:31:43,930
a decision
has finally been made.

1220
01:31:44,165 --> 01:31:47,501
The 1976 Japanese Grand Prix
will go ahead.

1221
01:31:48,636 --> 01:31:51,204
All drivers
to your cars, please.

1222
01:32:15,663 --> 01:32:17,564
Five minutes to go.

1223
01:32:59,974 --> 01:33:01,575
- All right?
- All right.

1224
01:33:01,809 --> 01:33:03,977
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1225
01:33:04,211 --> 01:33:05,645
To let the condensation out.

1226
01:33:05,880 --> 01:33:08,515
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1227
01:33:08,749 --> 01:33:11,851
Trust me, this race is all
about the start.

1228
01:33:12,520 --> 01:33:15,121
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1229
01:33:29,870 --> 01:33:31,972
Okay, start the bastard.

1230
01:33:34,208 --> 01:33:35,742
Good luck, kid.

1231
01:33:38,045 --> 01:33:39,646
Good luck, James!

1232
01:34:17,985 --> 01:34:19,919
30 seconds to go.

1233
01:34:39,874 --> 01:34:41,941
Electric tension here at Fuji.

1234
01:34:42,176 --> 01:34:44,411
80,000 bedraggled race fans

1235
01:34:44,645 --> 01:34:47,547
and the racing grudge match
of the decade.

1236
01:34:47,782 --> 01:34:49,783
And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,

1237
01:34:50,017 --> 01:34:51,951
James Hunt alongside him.

1238
01:34:53,154 --> 01:34:55,155
On row two of the grid,

1239
01:34:55,389 --> 01:34:56,723
there is Niki Lauda,

1240
01:34:56,957 --> 01:34:59,559
and on row three of the grid,
Joe Schecketer from South Africa

1241
01:34:59,794 --> 01:35:01,027
in the six-wheel Tyrrell.

1242
01:35:01,262 --> 01:35:04,164
Behind him, the rest
of the 25-car field.

1243
01:35:21,182 --> 01:35:23,750
There's the flag and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix

1244
01:35:23,984 --> 01:35:25,518
is underway!

1245
01:35:37,898 --> 01:35:40,366
In this conditions it must be
almost impossible

1246
01:35:40,601 --> 01:35:43,169
to drive a 450-horsepower car!

1247
01:36:10,097 --> 01:36:12,132
And it's Andretti
who has the lead,

1248
01:36:12,366 --> 01:36:13,566
but Hunt is attacking.

1249
01:36:13,801 --> 01:36:15,802
Hunt's going round
the outside ofAndretti!

1250
01:36:16,036 --> 01:36:17,670
Niki Lauda
following him through!

1251
01:36:17,905 --> 01:36:20,740
Hunt leads into the first
right-hander!

1252
01:37:03,450 --> 01:37:06,486
Hunt comes through to complete
his first lap leading the field.

1253
01:37:06,720 --> 01:37:08,655
At least he has clear vision
in front of him.

1254
01:37:08,889 --> 01:37:11,691
Niki Lauda behind him,
eating his spray.

1255
01:37:30,845 --> 01:37:32,111
Lauda is slowing!

1256
01:37:32,346 --> 01:37:36,082
Niki Lauda is bringing
the Ferrari no. 1 into the pit!

1257
01:37:36,784 --> 01:37:39,452
Some sort of problem,
we can't imagine what,

1258
01:37:39,687 --> 01:37:41,521
so early in the race.

1259
01:37:46,260 --> 01:37:50,163
What's wrong with the car?

1260
01:37:50,831 --> 01:37:52,832
Niki! What's wrong with the car?

1261
01:37:53,067 --> 01:37:55,168
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1262
01:37:59,540 --> 01:38:00,940
What are you doing?

1263
01:38:01,175 --> 01:38:02,041
I'm stopping.

1264
01:38:02,276 --> 01:38:04,110
His mechanics are asking
what the problem is.

1265
01:38:04,345 --> 01:38:06,679
But wait! Niki Lauda's
getting out of the car!

1266
01:38:06,914 --> 01:38:08,448
This is sensational!

1267
01:38:08,682 --> 01:38:10,617
The reigning World Champion,
Niki Lauda,

1268
01:38:10,851 --> 01:38:12,385
is out of this race.

1269
01:38:12,620 --> 01:38:13,953
It's too dangerous.

1270
01:38:14,188 --> 01:38:15,755
Niki, you want me to say

1271
01:38:15,990 --> 01:38:18,324
there was a problem
with the car, for the media?

1272
01:38:18,559 --> 01:38:19,392
No.

1273
01:38:20,561 --> 01:38:21,961
Tell them the truth.

1274
01:38:22,663 --> 01:38:24,430
Now, what is happening?

1275
01:38:24,665 --> 01:38:26,399
They're talking
to the team manager.

1276
01:38:26,634 --> 01:38:28,935
Lauda explaining something.

1277
01:38:43,651 --> 01:38:46,686
With Lauda out, James Hunt
knows he has to finish

1278
01:38:46,921 --> 01:38:50,723
this race in third place
or higher to be World Champion.

1279
01:38:50,958 --> 01:38:53,693
But the job's not done yet
for James Hunt.

1280
01:38:53,928 --> 01:38:55,495
In these dreadful conditions,

1281
01:38:55,729 --> 01:38:58,131
he still has to go the distance.

1282
01:38:59,466 --> 01:39:01,567
Fifteen laps to go
here at Fuji.

1283
01:39:01,802 --> 01:39:03,603
James Hunt or Niki Lauda?

1284
01:39:03,837 --> 01:39:06,673
This extraordinary season
is not over yet.

1285
01:39:06,907 --> 01:39:10,109
In this treacherous final round,
can James Hunt hang on?

1286
01:39:14,214 --> 01:39:15,882
Hunt in the lead.

1287
01:39:17,217 --> 01:39:19,786
Oh, God, his tyres,
they're blistering.

1288
01:39:20,721 --> 01:39:24,524
Brambilla very close behind him,
closing on him all the time.

1289
01:39:24,758 --> 01:39:27,860
And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.

1290
01:39:28,095 --> 01:39:30,830
Hunt cuts across
the orange March nose.

1291
01:39:31,065 --> 01:39:32,865
Hunt not having that at all.
And he's spinning.

1292
01:39:33,100 --> 01:39:36,636
He missed Hunt but almost took
James Hunt out of the race

1293
01:39:36,870 --> 01:39:38,671
and out
of the world championship.

1294
01:39:38,906 --> 01:39:42,141
Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.

1295
01:39:46,613 --> 01:39:48,648
Mario Andretti's
going past Hunt!

1296
01:39:48,882 --> 01:39:51,884
Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.

1297
01:39:57,157 --> 01:39:58,791
Despite this wet conditions,

1298
01:39:59,026 --> 01:40:01,561
these wet-weather tyres
wear extremely fast.

1299
01:40:01,795 --> 01:40:03,496
Hunt's tyres, they're gone.

1300
01:40:03,731 --> 01:40:06,933
Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.

1301
01:40:08,936 --> 01:40:11,771
That back marker's
going past Hunt.

1302
01:40:12,006 --> 01:40:14,240
LAP 70
4 LAPS TO GO

1303
01:40:23,083 --> 01:40:26,419
Look at that left front tyre,
right front tyre, sorry.

1304
01:40:26,653 --> 01:40:29,689
No tread on it at all.
And the other one is flat.

1305
01:40:29,923 --> 01:40:31,257
Let's go! Let's go!

1306
01:40:36,230 --> 01:40:38,765
Okay? When did you break
your gear lever?

1307
01:40:38,999 --> 01:40:40,566
Nine or ten laps ago.

1308
01:40:40,801 --> 01:40:42,935
- Alistair, we need to lift it!
- Come on!

1309
01:40:43,170 --> 01:40:44,704
- At the front!
- Let's go!

1310
01:40:44,938 --> 01:40:47,774
Regazzoni's Ferrari and
Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier

1311
01:40:48,008 --> 01:40:49,509
have gone ahead.

1312
01:40:49,743 --> 01:40:51,010
Come on, hurry!

1313
01:40:51,578 --> 01:40:54,680
You did it. You're going
to be World Champion!

1314
01:40:55,215 --> 01:40:56,082
Not yet.

1315
01:40:56,316 --> 01:40:59,685
A few laps ago, James Hunt
was looking like champion elect.

1316
01:40:59,920 --> 01:41:02,688
Now it looks as though
it's all gone wrong for him.

1317
01:41:04,124 --> 01:41:05,425
- James.
- Come on!

1318
01:41:05,659 --> 01:41:06,559
- Listen.
- What?

1319
01:41:06,794 --> 01:41:08,928
Just go easy out there.

1320
01:41:09,163 --> 01:41:12,832
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1321
01:41:13,067 --> 01:41:15,068
We want you back in one piece.

1322
01:41:15,302 --> 01:41:18,438
You're too far back. There's too
many drivers in front of you.

1323
01:41:18,672 --> 01:41:21,941
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1324
01:41:22,976 --> 01:41:23,910
Clear!

1325
01:41:24,545 --> 01:41:25,478
James!

1326
01:41:27,147 --> 01:41:29,115
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1327
01:41:33,520 --> 01:41:36,189
James Hunt rejoins the race
in sixth position.

1328
01:41:36,423 --> 01:41:40,526
There are four laps to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit.

1329
01:42:00,147 --> 01:42:01,714
Concentrate, Superstar.

1330
01:42:01,949 --> 01:42:03,716
Just brings it back
under control!

1331
01:42:03,951 --> 01:42:06,786
Sliding the McLaren
on the very edge there.

1332
01:42:08,722 --> 01:42:11,457
Hunt's M23 twitching this way
and that under braking.

1333
01:42:11,692 --> 01:42:12,825
And he almost loses it
right there.

1334
01:42:13,060 --> 01:42:14,427
Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte

1335
01:42:14,661 --> 01:42:16,095
in the blue Ligier.

1336
01:42:23,737 --> 01:42:25,471
Don't do it, James.

1337
01:42:28,008 --> 01:42:29,642
He's inches away
from the pit wall!

1338
01:42:29,877 --> 01:42:31,878
He's inches away
from the Ligier!

1339
01:42:40,854 --> 01:42:42,922
James Hunt has made up
another place,

1340
01:42:43,157 --> 01:42:46,192
but it's not enough
and this race is running out.

1341
01:42:54,668 --> 01:42:57,570
And Watson has spun!
Watson has spun!

1342
01:43:00,941 --> 01:43:03,843
Hunt manages to weave his way
between the back marker

1343
01:43:04,077 --> 01:43:06,112
and the stationary Penske.

1344
01:43:06,346 --> 01:43:08,748
He's catching Regazzoni,
but in these conditions,

1345
01:43:08,982 --> 01:43:12,485
it's one thing to catch up,
quite another to overtake.

1346
01:43:15,656 --> 01:43:18,090
He's alongside Clay Regazzoni!
This could be

1347
01:43:18,325 --> 01:43:20,126
the world championship!

1348
01:43:27,834 --> 01:43:29,535
He's got him!

1349
01:43:44,985 --> 01:43:46,719
Hunt crosses the line.

1350
01:43:46,954 --> 01:43:49,822
He needed to finish third
to score enough points

1351
01:43:50,057 --> 01:43:51,424
to be World Champion,

1352
01:43:51,658 --> 01:43:53,759
and in the confusion here
we're being told

1353
01:43:53,994 --> 01:43:55,494
that he may have finished 5th.

1354
01:43:55,729 --> 01:43:56,729
He finished fifth?

1355
01:43:57,998 --> 01:44:00,466
Our lap charts show Hunt
in third place.

1356
01:44:00,701 --> 01:44:02,335
Well, if the scoreboard's right,

1357
01:44:02,569 --> 01:44:04,971
it means he's just missed out
on the championship.

1358
01:44:05,205 --> 01:44:08,708
Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.

1359
01:44:12,713 --> 01:44:14,847
I can see the race stewards
conferring,

1360
01:44:15,082 --> 01:44:17,116
examining
the official lap charts.

1361
01:44:17,351 --> 01:44:20,453
We're just going to have to wait
for their verdict here.

1362
01:44:37,137 --> 01:44:38,471
Let's get you
out of here, buddy.

1363
01:44:38,705 --> 01:44:40,740
I'm sorry, Teddy. I thought
I could make up the ground.

1364
01:44:40,974 --> 01:44:42,842
Sorry? What are you
talking about? You did it!

1365
01:44:43,076 --> 01:44:45,745
- Did what?
- Jesus! You crazy bastard!

1366
01:44:45,979 --> 01:44:48,381
You came 3rd!
You got the points!

1367
01:44:48,615 --> 01:44:50,016
You're champion of the world!

1368
01:44:50,250 --> 01:44:53,052
James Hunt is now
officially confirmed

1369
01:44:53,287 --> 01:44:55,655
as finishing third
here in Japan,

1370
01:44:55,889 --> 01:44:59,025
and that means he
is champion of the world.

1371
01:45:00,761 --> 01:45:03,329
Our new World Champion,
James Hunt,

1372
01:45:03,563 --> 01:45:05,965
by just one single point.

1373
01:45:11,805 --> 01:45:13,673
Did we really win?

1374
01:45:16,777 --> 01:45:18,911
World bloody Champion!

1375
01:45:27,721 --> 01:45:31,557
- What are you going to do now?
- I shall be getting drunk.

1376
01:45:32,559 --> 01:45:34,994
It's wonderful, absolute dream.

1377
01:46:21,541 --> 01:46:25,044
And our special guest,
Formula 1 champion, James Hunt.

1378
01:46:25,278 --> 01:46:27,813
JAMES HUNT
WORLD CHAMPION

1379
01:46:37,758 --> 01:46:39,759
JAMES HUNT
AGAINST ALL ODDS

1380
01:46:49,636 --> 01:46:51,637
Wait. Come on.

1381
01:46:54,207 --> 01:46:57,543
There's no better motor oil
than Havoline.

1382
01:47:08,455 --> 01:47:11,624
- Yes, me too. Where we going?
- Anywhere I want to go.

1383
01:47:11,858 --> 01:47:14,093
And I don't have
to hijack it, either.

1384
01:47:14,327 --> 01:47:16,362
As long as I pay for it.

1385
01:47:16,596 --> 01:47:18,898
I'm starving.
Let's get some food.

1386
01:47:29,609 --> 01:47:31,444
- Where are you going?
- You lot go ahead.

1387
01:47:31,678 --> 01:47:33,446
I won't be a minute.

1388
01:47:35,015 --> 01:47:35,948
Niki!

1389
01:47:38,985 --> 01:47:40,453
Good to see you!

1390
01:47:44,791 --> 01:47:46,625
I heard you were spending
more and more time

1391
01:47:46,860 --> 01:47:48,861
- in one of these.
- Do you fly?

1392
01:47:49,095 --> 01:47:49,862
No.

1393
01:47:50,096 --> 01:47:52,598
- I don't think they'd insure me.
- You should try.

1394
01:47:52,833 --> 01:47:53,833
It's good for discipline.

1395
01:47:54,067 --> 01:47:55,401
You have to stay
within the rules,

1396
01:47:55,635 --> 01:47:57,102
stick to regulation,
suppress the ego.

1397
01:47:57,337 --> 01:47:59,038
It helps with the racing.

1398
01:47:59,272 --> 01:48:01,774
And there I was thinking
you were about to wax lyrical

1399
01:48:02,008 --> 01:48:05,444
- about the romance of flight.
- No, that's all bullshit.

1400
01:48:06,947 --> 01:48:08,681
So what brings you here?

1401
01:48:08,915 --> 01:48:10,449
A friend's wedding.

1402
01:48:10,684 --> 01:48:11,784
At least I think
it was a wedding.

1403
01:48:12,018 --> 01:48:13,018
Might have been a birthday
or something.

1404
01:48:13,253 --> 01:48:14,687
It's all a bit of a blur.

1405
01:48:14,921 --> 01:48:17,590
- Have you been at Fiorano?
- Pre-season testing.

1406
01:48:17,824 --> 01:48:19,558
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1407
01:48:19,793 --> 01:48:21,494
I'm not sure that was meant
as a compliment.

1408
01:48:21,728 --> 01:48:24,363
When do you start testing?
Next week?

1409
01:48:24,598 --> 01:48:26,065
No. What, are you nuts?

1410
01:48:26,299 --> 01:48:27,700
I didn't just win
the biggest thing of my life

1411
01:48:27,934 --> 01:48:30,002
so I could get
right back to work.

1412
01:48:30,237 --> 01:48:32,571
Why? You have to.

1413
01:48:33,240 --> 01:48:35,040
To prove to all the people

1414
01:48:35,275 --> 01:48:36,876
who will always say
you just won it because...

1415
01:48:37,110 --> 01:48:40,412
Because of what?
Because of your accident?

1416
01:48:41,581 --> 01:48:44,383
Niki, is that other people
or is that you?

1417
01:48:44,618 --> 01:48:45,784
I won, okay?

1418
01:48:46,019 --> 01:48:47,586
On the all-important day
when it came down to it,

1419
01:48:47,821 --> 01:48:50,523
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1420
01:48:50,757 --> 01:48:52,758
And I put my life on the line
and I saw it through.

1421
01:48:52,993 --> 01:48:54,793
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1422
01:48:55,028 --> 01:48:57,429
The risks were totally
unacceptable.

1423
01:48:57,664 --> 01:48:59,098
You were prepared to die.

1424
01:48:59,332 --> 01:49:01,634
- To me, that's losing.
- Yes, I was. I admit it.

1425
01:49:01,868 --> 01:49:04,470
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1426
01:49:04,704 --> 01:49:06,472
And that's the effect
you have on me.

1427
01:49:06,706 --> 01:49:09,642
You'd pushed me that far.
And it felt great!

1428
01:49:10,176 --> 01:49:12,678
I mean, hell, isn't that
what we're in this for?

1429
01:49:12,913 --> 01:49:15,581
To stare death in the face
and to cheat it?

1430
01:49:16,516 --> 01:49:18,484
Come on,
there's nobility in that.

1431
01:49:18,718 --> 01:49:20,486
It's like being knights.

1432
01:49:20,820 --> 01:49:23,088
You English,
you're such assholes.

1433
01:49:23,323 --> 01:49:25,357
You know my position.

1434
01:49:25,592 --> 01:49:26,592
20% risk.

1435
01:49:26,826 --> 01:49:29,361
No, Niki, don't bring
the percentages into this.

1436
01:49:29,596 --> 01:49:30,829
Don't be a pro.

1437
01:49:31,064 --> 01:49:33,566
The minute you do that,
you kill what's good about this.

1438
01:49:33,800 --> 01:49:35,434
You kill the sport.

1439
01:49:38,505 --> 01:49:41,440
James!

1440
01:49:45,145 --> 01:49:46,645
I've got to go.

1441
01:49:48,148 --> 01:49:50,182
Careful in this thing.

1442
01:49:51,184 --> 01:49:52,217
James.

1443
01:49:57,857 --> 01:50:01,427
In hospital, the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1444
01:50:01,928 --> 01:50:03,862
Pumping the shit
out of my lungs.

1445
01:50:04,097 --> 01:50:05,497
It was hell.

1446
01:50:05,966 --> 01:50:08,434
And while doing it,
I was watching television.

1447
01:50:08,668 --> 01:50:11,370
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1448
01:50:11,605 --> 01:50:14,373
"That bastard, Hunt," I'd say.
"I hate that guy."

1449
01:50:14,608 --> 01:50:16,141
And one day,
the doctor came and said,

1450
01:50:16,376 --> 01:50:18,777
"Mr. Lauda, may I offer
a piece of advice?"

1451
01:50:19,012 --> 01:50:21,013
"Stop thinking of it as a curse
to have been given

1452
01:50:21,247 --> 01:50:22,615
an enemy in life."

1453
01:50:22,849 --> 01:50:24,617
"It can be blessing too."

1454
01:50:24,851 --> 01:50:26,185
"A wise man gets more
from his enemies

1455
01:50:26,419 --> 01:50:28,087
than a fool from his friends."

1456
01:50:28,321 --> 01:50:30,956
And you know what?
He was right.

1457
01:50:32,892 --> 01:50:34,093
Look at us.

1458
01:50:34,327 --> 01:50:36,795
We were both a pair of kids
when we met.

1459
01:50:37,030 --> 01:50:39,064
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1460
01:50:39,299 --> 01:50:42,267
Disowned by our families.
Headed nowhere.

1461
01:50:42,969 --> 01:50:45,704
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1462
01:50:45,939 --> 01:50:47,506
It was not bad.

1463
01:50:47,907 --> 01:50:49,808
No, it's not bad.

1464
01:50:50,043 --> 01:50:51,977
So don't let me down now.

1465
01:50:52,212 --> 01:50:53,879
I need you busting my balls.

1466
01:50:54,114 --> 01:50:56,982
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1467
01:50:57,550 --> 01:50:59,785
But I intend to enjoy
myself first.

1468
01:51:00,020 --> 01:51:02,354
Some of life needs to be
for pleasure.

1469
01:51:02,589 --> 01:51:05,557
What's the point of having a
million cups, medals and planes

1470
01:51:05,792 --> 01:51:08,127
if you don't have any fun?

1471
01:51:08,628 --> 01:51:10,863
How is that winning?

1472
01:51:11,831 --> 01:51:14,566
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1473
01:51:14,801 --> 01:51:15,668
James!

1474
01:51:19,839 --> 01:51:21,974
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1475
01:51:23,043 --> 01:51:24,176
You will...

1476
01:51:24,644 --> 01:51:25,577
champ.

1477
01:51:27,814 --> 01:51:29,882
You look good, Niki.

1478
01:51:30,116 --> 01:51:33,852
The only guy to have burnt his
face and it be an improvement.

1479
01:51:39,793 --> 01:51:42,461
Of course he didn't
listen to me.

1480
01:51:42,762 --> 01:51:45,864
For James, one world title
was enough.

1481
01:51:46,099 --> 01:51:48,967
He had proved
what he needed to prove,

1482
01:51:49,269 --> 01:51:52,805
to himself
and anyone who doubted him.

1483
01:51:53,740 --> 01:51:56,475
And two years later he retired.

1484
01:51:56,710 --> 01:51:59,778
When I saw him next
in London seven years later,

1485
01:52:00,146 --> 01:52:02,114
me as champion again,

1486
01:52:02,348 --> 01:52:03,849
him as broadcaster,

1487
01:52:04,084 --> 01:52:07,853
he was barefoot on a bicycle,
with a flat tyre.

1488
01:52:08,488 --> 01:52:11,590
Still living each day
like his last.

1489
01:52:12,792 --> 01:52:16,595
When I heard he'd died aged 45,
of a heart attack,

1490
01:52:16,930 --> 01:52:18,864
I wasn't surprised.

1491
01:52:19,499 --> 01:52:21,500
I was just sad.

1492
01:52:22,035 --> 01:52:24,970
People always think of us
as rivals,

1493
01:52:25,538 --> 01:52:28,707
but he was among
the very few I liked

1494
01:52:29,576 --> 01:52:32,444
and even fewer
that I respected.

1495
01:52:35,648 --> 01:52:38,717
He remains the only person
I envied.

1496
